cs.NI, cs.HC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.EM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the communication aspects of Wireless Body Area Networks (WBAN) and the impact of path loss on communication. This makes cs.NI the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper focuses on the application of WBAN in Ubiquitous Healthcare (UHC) and how it can benefit elderly people. This makes cs.HC a likely sub-category.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses different standards used in WBAN and their impact on communication. This makes cs.IT a likely sub-category.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the system on chip and low power sensor nodes used in WBAN. This makes cs.SY a possible sub-category.
5. cs.EM (Emerging Technologies) - The paper discusses the advances in wireless communication and low power sensor nodes that have enabled the realization of WBAN. This makes cs.EM a possible sub-category.
